Package popt4jlib

popt4jlib: a parallel optimization library for Java.

See:
          Description

Interface Summary
AllChromosomeMakerClonableIntf interface specifying that AllChromosomeMakerIntf objects can be cloned.
AllChromosomeMakerIntf allows the definition of the neighborhood of a point in a search space that is needed by Local-Search algorithms in combinatorial optimization problems.
Arg2ChromosomeMakerIntf interface defining the methods that an object must support so as to be able to convert a function argument (an object type that the function being minimized accepts) into a chromosome object (notion used in GA, SA, PS, EA meta-heuristics among others).
Chromosome2ArgMakerIntf the inverse map of the Arg2ChromosomeMakerIntf.
FunctionIntf interface defining a function mapping objects of some domain (not necessarily R^n) to R.
IdentifiableIntf interface declares that implementing objects have long identifier.
NewChromosomeMakerIntf allows the creation of a new Object that will play the role of a chromosome in algorithms such as GA,EA,PS, etc. using a starting point Title: popt4jlib Description: A Parallel Meta-Heuristic Optimization Library in Java Copyright: Copyright (c) 2011 Company:
ObserverIntf This interface allows objects that want to be "monitoring" other "Subject" objects to be notified whenever a change in the subject occurs, and act accordingly.
OptimizerIntf the interface every optimizer (for unconstrained optimization) must implement.
PoolableObjectIntf interface specifies the contract for objects that can participate in thread-local object pools.
RandomArgMakerClonableIntf interface specifying that RandomArgMakerIntf objects can be cloned.
RandomArgMakerIntf interface class for constructing random arguments for a function.
RandomChromosomeMakerIntf interface class for constructing random chromosome objects used in meta- heuristics such as GA,EA,PS,MC,SA etc.
SparseVectorIntf this interface extends the standard VectorIntf in that it provides two methods to allow for (fast) loops over the non-zero elements of a sparse vector.
SubjectIntf The SubjectIntf implements the Subject Object's methods in the well-known Observer Design Pattern.
VecFunctionIntf definition of a vector function mapping vectors in R^n to vectors in R^m Title: popt4jlib Description: A Parallel Meta-Heuristic Optimization Library in Java Copyright: Copyright (c) 2011 Company:
VectorIntf defines vectors in R^n Title: popt4jlib Description: A Parallel Meta-Heuristic Optimization Library in Java Copyright: Copyright (c) 2011 Company:
 

Class Summary
Constants class defines compile-time constants useful in the methods of the classes in the parallel package, as well as in the Debug class in the utils package.
DblArray1SparseVector sparse double[] implementation of VectorIntf, maintaining two arrays, an index array, and a values array.
DblArray1SparseVectorFE sparse double[] implementation of SparseVectorIntf, maintaining two arrays, an index array, and the FULL length values array.
DblArray1SparseVectorMT sparse double[] implementation of VectorIntf, maintaining two arrays, an index array, and a values array.
DblArray1Vector double[] implementation of VectorIntf.
DblArray1VectorMaker class responsible for converting double[] chromosome objects into DblArray1Vector arguments for functions having as domain VectorIntf objects.
DblArray1VectorThreadLocalPools auxiliary class using the ThreadLocal mechanism to create thread-local DblArray1Vector object pools.
FltArray1SparseVector sparse float[] implementation of VectorIntf, maintaining two arrays, an index array, and a values array.
FunctionBase The class is a wrapper class for FunctionIntf objects, that keeps track of how many times a function has been evaluated.
FunctionEvaluationTask auxiliary class used when the user requests function evaluations to be executed in separate threads in a thread-pool for a limited time so as to avoid "locking-up" the minimization process by function evaluations that take too long to complete (such evaluations are "lost" by the minimization process even if they eventually complete).
GLockingObservableObserverBase base class implementing both the SubjectIntf and ObserverIntf interfaces, with all implemented methods locking on the global "popt4jlib" w-lock.
GLockingObserverBase base class implementing only the ObserverIntf interface -template method style-, with the implemented method locking on the global "popt4jlib" w-lock.
IdentityArg2CMaker class implements the identity Arg->;Chromosome transformation.
IdentityC2ArgMaker class implements the identity Chromosome->;Arg transformation.
IntArray1SparseVector sparse int[] implementation of VectorIntf, maintaining two arrays, an index array, and a values array.
LimitedTimeEvalFunction The class is a wrapper class for FunctionIntf objects, that forces the function to execute in a different thread than the calling thread, allowing only up to a certain amount of time for execution.
ReentrantFunctionBase The class is a wrapper class for FunctionIntf objects, that keeps track of how many times a function has been evaluated, plus it forces threads asking for function evaluation to execute sequentially.
ReentrantFunctionBaseMT The class is a wrapper class for FunctionIntf objects, that keeps track of how many times a function has been evaluated, plus it forces threads asking for function evaluation to execute using a different FunctionIntf object, so that no calls from different threads execute on the same FunctionIntf object (this way, if the eval() call modifies only NON-static data members of the FunctionIntf object, there is no data race danger.)
ReentrantSocketEvalFunctionBase The class is a wrapper for functions that are computed in a different process and communicate with the optimizer through sockets.
ShiftedArgFunctionBase The class is a wrapper class for FunctionIntf objects, that evaluates the FunctionIntf object not on the actual VectorIntf or double[] argument x that it is given, but rather on a shifted vector x-&delta, where the shift &delta is passed in the params hashtable as a pair <"function.shiftarg", double[] delta>.
 

Exception Summary
OptimizerException Exception class used by most optimization algorithms in the popt4jlib package to indicate abnormal execution of some task.
 

Package popt4jlib Description

popt4jlib: a parallel optimization library for Java.

Package Specification

A parallel (multi-threaded) version of a number of optimization algorithms and meta-heuristics for optimization in Java. The algorithms implemented include: Genetic Algorithms (island model), Simulated Annealing, Evolutionary Algorithms, Differential Evolution, Monte-Carlo (random) Search, Particle Swarm Optimization, Gradient-Descent methods including Steepest-Descent and Conjugate-Gradient, and several graph-optimization algorithms including Shortest-Path problems, Weighted Clique problems, Minimum Spanning Tree problems etc.
